metadata.name: Purgatory #2
metadata.description:
Purgatory is a place where the souls of those who have died in a state of grace are purified from venial sins or from the temporal punishment which still remains to be endured. As such, it is seen as a temporary and final purification that brings about the achievement of the holiness necessary to enter the joy of heaven.

Click to fly around and explore your personal purgatory.

metadata.name: Retroscapes #150
metadata.description:
You are approaching newly discovered planetary ring system, seen by no human before.
Gravity works in strange ways there. Intrigued, you grab your polaroid. 
Snap, and there it is - your grainy Retroscape.

Beauty comes from diversity.

Size of the collection - 222 pieces - is a tribute to my first NFT.

metadata.name: FxPlanet #719
metadata.description:
🟢〰Storyline〰🟢

Once upon a time, a God had a little daughter. The daughter liked to explore the planets on his father's cosmos. Suddenly the daughter got sick and died like a collapsing star. God gets alone, angry, depressed and finally mad. He turned all the universe to ash and mixed the ash of her daughter's soul with it to make her alive, But he failed. In the end, he decided to destroy himself to make a New cosmos of all generative planets from ash of himself and his daughter's soul to one more time in the eternity they can be with each other in a heart of a planet. If you listen carefully to the planets, you may hear them calling each other.

⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛

🔴〰Rarity〰🔴

This collection is a 3D generative interactive artwork (Made with Unity Game Engine) that contains of 9999+1 planets (1 shared source of light and 9999 pieces of souls) from billions of variation. You can see more random variations from fxhash page.
◼ The beauty and complexity of the Planet's surface is important, But what is going on inside?
Each planet has three grades of volume (High, Medium, Low) that show you what resources exist on the planets (Common, Rare, Legendary).
Some resources are so valuable and infrequent.
◼ For Example: It's possible to get Oxygen (Legendary Resource) on Low volume slot, but it's infrequent if you get it on High volume slot.
◼ Checkout Material rarity list on webpage.

📎 Webpage address: HashProtocol.tez.page

⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛

🔵〰Social〰🔵

◼ Participant in events or get achievements to win some prizes.
So it's significant to see you on the discord server. Checkout rarity table, achievements rewards, … on the webpage.
📎 Webpage address: HashProtocol.tez.page

⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛⬛

🟠〰Interact〰🟠

◼ You can rotate around of planets by “WASD” keys on the keyboard or arrow keys.
◼ Zoom In by “E” key and Zoom Out by “Q”.
◼ Full HD texture by Key “1”.
◼ 4k texture by Key “2”.
◼ 8k texture by Key “3”.

metadata.name: Emotional Shell #411
metadata.description:
Manual Dutch Auction (DA): 72 · 54 · 40 · 30 · 24 · 20 every 8 minutes.
Auction will stop changing price when non-reserves are fully minted, and then drop one price tier.

---------

The feeling of being human – with all of its intricate hopes, struggles, and fleeting emotions – seems so unique that we assume artificial intelligence could never replicate our experience. And while we devise systems for solving unfathomably complex problems, generating algorithmic creativity, and unlocking regenerative biological possibilities, we simultaneously cling to the power and originality of emotional feeling – believing it to be the irreplaceable source of what makes us human.

If the body is our shell for emotion and soul, can an artificial humanoid be another vessel for these thoughts and feelings – for human essence itself? If our ‘soul’ is the last stand between us and the machines, what happens when the soul becomes transferable? That we may see answers to these questions looks more real every year, and is perhaps a little frightening. 

Emotional Shell uses introspective portraits of future selves to question what it means to be human, when the people around us are no longer human.

---------

Warning: This piece is GPU intensive, it may not render on lower end devices.

Press 1-3 to select from low, medium, and high quality settings
Press 'S' to save the image at the current scale
Press 'H' to save the image at 2400px resolution

Created with Three.js
For third party license information, please see bundle.js.LICENSE.txt

---------

TENDER x wwatkns
August 2022

metadata.name: Composition #4 #2
metadata.description:
When I'm working on a problem, I never think about beauty. But when I've finished, if the solution is not beautiful... I know it's wrong.
[Buckminster Fuller]

I tried to hybridize, in a schematic way only, the architectural language of neoplasticism with some characteristics of Islamic architecture. The result seems to me to convey a certain elegance...
As with the other "Composition #" series, you can explore the model interactively in 3D space.

metadata.name: RGB Elementary Cellular Automaton #899
metadata.description:
Stephen Wolfram's Elementary Cellular Automaton where 3 different rules are drawn in the Red, Green and Blue color components of the image.

Rules are selected randomly among a pre-selection of 53 rules from which nice behaviors emerge.

Tokens can have a cell size in the [1; 20] range.

metadata.name: Botanical Gardens #35
metadata.description:
Question shouldn't be, What is Art?
Just because the answer is quite simple, imagination and creation to inspire.
The question should be, What is Art without dimensions, colors, shades, inspiration, creativity, vibrancy, variations, etc... "NOTHING", we get above all from God's Creation(Art) and no man can ever be a bigger artist than God. 

I always had attraction towards the flowers, the colors, the creativity, the fragrance, all have enticed me to appreciate what we are blessed with.

Botanical Gardens is all about dimensions, colors, vibrancy, and variations.
In this project we go deep with sin & cos to generate patterns of flowers, in comes the Botany's premium color themes range which cover from fade to vibrant colors. Add with some onclick variations, you can always find the best possible locations for your flowers and save.

This project is token of my appreciation to God for blessing us all, with this amazing art surrounding us.

Click on NFT to see the flower dance.
Press "S" to save 1000x1000 png of your mint.
You are welcome to request a Hi-Res image for your holdings via twitter @TheRealBotany
